abstracts.cdata!:
The Third Highway Project has four
            principal components: (a) construction of two highway
            sections totalling 124 km to two-lane paved standard and two
            bridges between Menado, the capital of North Sulawesi, and a
            rice-producing area under development in the Dumoga Valley;
            (b) feasibility study of approximately 300 km of highway
            between Bandung and Cilicap in Java and 250 km of related
            feeder roads, and subsequent detailed engineering if
            justified; (c) technical assistance to DGH to prepare a
            program for the betterment of existing low-standard
            highways; (d) training of highway maintenance personnel.
